          <td width="405" class="texte">
FULL TIME POSITION, Bordeaux France<BR><BR><BR>Principle duties and responsibilities<BR> <BR>·	You will manage our computer network (PC, printers and all software) :  follow-up, installation, and inventory <BR><BR>·	You will manage the administration of the internal network : creation of personal accounts and rights, follow-up of the email server, switches, hubs…<BR><BR>·	You will give technical support to users for internal network and software issues : both troubleshooting and training <BR><BR>·	Working with the Network Administrator, you will manage the administration of both Windows and Linux servers<BR><BR>Education, experience and skills required<BR><BR>·	You have 2 years experience in a similar position, and have good network management skills (knowledge of Windows 2000, XP, TCP/IP) <BR><BR>·	You are extremely organised, methodical as well as particularly reliable <BR><BR>·	You enjoy having a good degree of responsibility. You are a proactive individual, extremely concerned by the very specific needs of IN FUSIO <BR><BR>·	You are an excellent problem solver and you regularly propose new solutions, as well as showing strong pedagogical skills <BR><BR>·	You are fluent in English.<BR><BR><BR>If you are flexible, dynamic and eager to be a member of a very international team (English is the working language) and if you are motivated to contribute to the further growth of this innovative company then please send us your CV.<BR><BR>We feel it is very important to help develop the skills of all our employees.<BR>Thus, in order to help you along your career path, we do our<BR>best to maximize the possibility of internal promotion.<BR><BR><BR>
